#: ../../content/guides/api-mode.md:1
msgid "API Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/api-mode.md:6
msgid ""
"Running releng-tool can be invoked in an \"API mode\" where an execution "
"will generate a programmatic response for a caller. When in an API mode, the"
" resulting standard output stream will contain a JSON-compatible output for "
"external applications to process. All other messages that may typically be "
"generated on the standard output stream will instead be written to the "
"standard error stream."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/api-mode.md:13
msgid "Running releng-tool with `--api` enables API mode for that run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/api-mode.md:19
msgid ""
"Responses may vary on the action and other options used. Callers will always"
" get a `code` response (matching the return value):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/api-mode.md:29
msgid ""
"There is no definitive schema for this output at this time. Results may vary"
" as this feature evolves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/api-mode.md:32
msgid ""
"Due to the flexibility of how projects/extensions can manipulate a run and "
"generate data on the standard output stream, it is recommended that "
"developers utilize logging calls provided by this tooling to ensure the "
"standard output stream is not populated during an API mode run."
msgstr ""

